ave value in themselves, not only as habitat for sentient beings — a belief most people say they hold, so it rides early on the train. Not a sentience claim: the value is what non-market existence-value / willingness-to-pay studies say people who hold nature intrinsically valuable place on it (cross-checked by the sacrifice environmental movements make), converted to wDALY. Where animals do not dominate the circle, habitat protection (Rainforest Trust) can win. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 nature_intrinsic_value" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_3.drawio" id="w1_2_3"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f2e3b3;strokeColor=#c9a72a;fontColor=#57450e;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="-0" y="271" width="280" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Climate damages are&lt;br&gt;civilizational-scale&lt;br&gt;[1+2+4]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;   24 lives-eq/$1k · 98% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Clean Air Task Force · 2%&lt;br&gt;▼ 39 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + climate_tipping_points&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Climate change is a civilizational-scale welfare loss, not a marginal externality: Bressler&#x27;s mortality cost of carbon (~1 death per 4,434 tCO2), PIK&#x27;s committed ~19% income loss by 2049 (Kotz, Levermann &amp; Wenz), and Rockström / Armstrong McKay tipping-element cascades amplifying both. Advocacy that cheaply averts emissions (Clean Air Task Force) enters the slate; where the chain also holds nature&#x27;s intrinsic value, protecting tropical forest — itself a tipping element — picks up the co-benefit. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 4 climate_tipping_points" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_4.drawio" id="w1_2_4"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f6e0c0;strokeColor=#c9932a;fontColor=#5a3f10;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="52" y="542" width="301" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Future humans count&lt;br&gt;(discounted)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;   24 lives-eq/$1k · 100% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up AIM / Charity Entrepreneurship · 0%&lt;br&gt;▼ 307 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Future people are inside the circle, but with a positive pure-time discount rate — the moderate longtermist position. A modest discount is enough to keep present, measurable global health competitive with future-protecting work; remove it (the next assumption) and the astronomical numbers take over. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5.drawio" id="w1_2_5"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f5d3b8;strokeColor=#cc7a33;fontColor=#5a300e;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="54" y="813" width="373" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+7]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;   21k lives-eq/$1k · 72% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Wild insects (humane pesticides) · 28%&lt;br&gt;▼ 15 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 7 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_7.drawio" id="w1_2_7"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#eec2a8;strokeColor=#c65a2e;fontColor=#5a2a10;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="106" y="1084" width="395" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Suffering-focused&lt;br&gt;ethics&lt;br&gt;[1+2+8]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;   73 lives-eq/$1k · 100% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up GiveWell top charity (AMF) · 0%&lt;br&gt;(Brian Tomasik, David Pearce)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + suffering_focused&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Asymmetry: averting intense suffering takes priority over creating happiness. Factory farming, malaria and the worst wild-animal conditions weigh up; speculative future-flourishing bets weigh down. Arises most naturally from taking animal suffering seriously, so it requires animals_somewhat. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 8 suffering_focused" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWH9z2zYS%2FSo7nvZOysg0Sf1Wzp1xYrnN1EkztnOdTpRxIBKSUFMEC4Cm1dTf%2FRYAKVIWPWZO%2F3hoEXj7dvctsMtvRyFdkDRSb3lIjyZHJydwenoKN4KwGBSHQJC%2FN%2FiQxTBLfdfrQcZFFN4zmkHm3fq3I2hJxRMYtfX